ALCOHOL CONTAMINATION, FATAL - RUSSIA (12): PSKOV, VOLGOGRAD
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1] Pskov
Date: 21 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org
Source: INFORMPskov, 19 Dec 2006 [translated by Mod.NR]
<http://informpskov.ru/society/31757.html>

There are currently 306 people at Pskov hospitals [with poisoning
from] counterfeit alcohol. According to chief hygiene and sanitary
physician Sergey Nikiforov, the total number of people suffering from
such contamination from 25 Oct to 19 Dec 2006 is 1059. From 18-19
Dec, 12 people were hospitalized for the same reason. One person died
during this period, and altogether 53 people have died as a result of
toxic hepatitis. Law enforcement agencies continue fighting against
counterfeit alcohol sales.
******
[2] Volgograd
Date: 21 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org
Source: Newsru, 18 Dec 2006 [translated by Mod.NR]
<http://www.regions.ru/news/2038053>

With 4 people hospitalized yesterday, 508 are currently hospitalized,
377 of whom are on ambulatory care, and 34 people have died as a
result of alcohol contamination. In 23 cases toxic hepatitis was the
confirmed diagnosis.
The 2 areas of Volgograd that are most severely affected by alcohol
contamination are Mihaylovskiy district with 371 cases, then
Frolovskiy region with 152 cases.
Medical prevention center staff are conducting regular interviews
with the population. It has been found that on average 19 percent of
men and 12 percent of women continue to buy alcohol from friends,
neighbors and unreliable sales points.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Alcohol contamination periodically affects parts of Russia. The
experts are forecasting the second "wave" of alcohol contamination
that will be associated with the New Year holidays. No regulations
will be able to prevent people from buying counterfeit alcohol. -
Mod.NR]
